220
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,880
And then you follow up with the educational or the selling.

221
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:27,519
Now that you have the attention, you want to teach something, give some free value, or pitch your product,

222
00:12:27,519 --> 00:12:29,680
but importantly from a place of goodwill.

223
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:33,279
So you say, for example, here's how you grow on X D with super X.

224
00:12:33,279 --> 00:12:35,760
And then the final part of the loop is to turn it inspirational.

225
00:12:35,760 --> 00:12:39,440
So at this point, probably got loads of views, maybe you got a few sales, few followers.

226
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,959
Take a screenshot of that, post it.

227
00:12:40,959 --> 00:12:42,639
That itself will potentially go viral.

228
00:12:42,639 --> 00:12:46,000
But importantly, if you want to have that impact, you want to share what it means to you.

229
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
For example, this is why I left my job.

230
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,360
Moments like this make it worth it.

231
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,399
But write it from the heart.

232
00:12:50,399 --> 00:12:52,480
You want people to root for your journey authentically.

233
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:55,440
And then once you're at the end of the loop, rinse back to the start and repeat.

234
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,560
This loop does three things.

235
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:58,800
It builds trust through authenticity.

236
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:04,160
It educates your audience so that they see the value that you bring and it sells without being annoying.

237
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:06,320
Step four is systemize what works.

238
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,560
This is kind of like my secret source if you want to call it that.

239
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:09,519
Don't guess what to post.

240
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:10,079
Use data.

241
00:13:10,079 --> 00:13:12,000
Go to successful profiles in your niche.

242
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,680
Analyze their top performing post.

243
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:16,959
So I use the superchrome extension for this, but you can use whatever is comfortable.

244
00:13:16,959 --> 00:13:21,040
And then identify the concept, most importantly the concept, not the actual post that worked.

245
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:24,959
So you want to take that concept, not word for word, and then make it in your own style.

246
00:13:24,959 --> 00:13:30,000
A real example in my case was I used SuperX to analyze what was going viral in my niche.

247
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,880
I found a curse for tweets and algorithm simulator were going viral.

248
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,399
So I built this features in SuperX.

249
00:13:34,399 --> 00:13:37,360
I posted the dancing demo showing them off and this worked.

250
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:41,600
It was combining the proven viral concept with my personality.

251
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,639
Step five, double down on what works and kill what doesn't.

252
00:13:44,639 --> 00:13:47,600
By this point, you're going to have some signal of what's working and what isn't.

253
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:50,480
So you should be tracking every single post's performance.

254
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,839
Then you want to find your patterns.

255
00:13:51,839 --> 00:13:53,920
So what format works best for me?

256
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,279
In my case, it was video for you.

257
00:13:55,279 --> 00:13:56,320
It might be something different.

258
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:58,480
What style of posting resonates?

259
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,240
And then what topics engage?

260
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:03,440
So in my case, it was feature releases and authentic moments.

261
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:06,079
Then when you find what works, make more of it.

262
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:09,360
Double down on what works cuz the algorithm rewards consistency.

263
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:12,800
And then importantly, also this is a part that a lot of people forget, kill what doesn't,

264
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,680
even if it went viral.

265
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:19,120
So in my case, algorithm simulator went viral, but I killed it from SuperX because it was a feature that most people didn't even use.

266
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:21,040
Step six is build real connections.

267
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:22,000
This is the crux of it all.

268
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:28,800
So far it feels very cold and calculated but at the end of the day you want to be building real connections like you build a real community in real life.

269
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:32,639
I see a lot of my audience and followers as genuine friends and they are genuine friends.

270
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:38,160
I've met up with them as I've been traveling through the world cuz the important thing is that growth isn't just through viral posts.

271
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:41,680
You shouldn't just be chasing virality assuming that you actually want to build something real.

272
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:44,560
You need to build a community through intentional engagement.

273
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:47,360
What most people do wrong is they focus on quantity.

274
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:51,199
So they use AI to spam replies under hundreds of posts, which is a huge problem.

275
00:14:51,199 --> 00:14:54,399
On X, they'll say generic comments like, "Ah, so great.

276
00:14:54,399 --> 00:14:55,120
Oh, wow.

277
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:55,760
Great post."

278
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:58,160
And at the end of the day, they get no real connections built.

279
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:06,160
But what actually works is you want to find people in your niche, in your community that you genuinely want to connect with and make friends with and then reply with real value.

280
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:11,920
Share your experience, share stories, ask thoughtful questions, and stay consistent with the same people like building any friendship in real life.

281
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:14,000
Show up daily, be yourself, not a robot.

282
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,800
And finally, step seven, leverage what the platform wants.

283
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,560
Right now, X is pushing video.

284
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:22,560
I don't know what it will be in the future, but video works really well because it keeps people on the platform longer.

285
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,959
They're watching your video, so videos get more reach.

286
00:15:24,959 --> 00:15:28,399
This does change over time, so you need to pay attention and adapt.

287
00:15:28,399 --> 00:15:32,720
For me, when I switched from text to video format, I got 10 times the reach of text posts.

288
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:38,560
But the bottom line of all of this is that unlike what I thought was the case, it isn't about luck.

289
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:43,680
is about building trust through consistent storytelling, systemizing virality through data and analytics,

290
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:46,320
and focusing on building intentional, real friendships.

291
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:48,320
If you do this, you won't need paid ads.

